 them to learn or, in some cases, even have equality. %0a%3c %0a%3c The idea that the deaf could not learn was accepted until the sixteenth century, when philosophers and teachers, including Girolamo Cardano, finally wished to prove that Aristotle was wrong. Cardano created his own signing code, which, although it never reached large amounts of people, he used to teach his own deaf son how to communicate. At a similar time, Pedro Ponce de Leon, a Spanish monk, taught several deaf students how to read, write, and speak in order for them to become properly integrated members of society that could eventually claim their own inheritances (this was not possible for those that were unable to communicate). The work of Cardano and Leon, among others, would inspire Juan Pablo de Bonet to create his own book on sign language, with a guide on how to sign the alphabet and certain sounds. This book would be key to the creation of official sign language systems in the eighteenth century, which are the earliest forms of the modern sign language systems used today.%0a%3c %0a%3c https://get.goreact.com/resources/the-history-of-sign-language/%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:elseif [ equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:andrewid} '' || equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:section} '' ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c You must enter your andrew ID and section before submitting an expansion. %0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c (:if equal {$Author} {$:Author}:)%0a%3c !!Change article category%0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#changearticlecategory:)%0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c (:Section: F